expansion.name_gatherer: Heads I Win, Tails You Lose

cards.name: Fabricate
cards.text: Search your library for an artifact card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
cards.flavor:
"I'm one masterpiece away from ruling this pathetic world."
-Saldrath, master artificer

cards.name: Negate
cards.text: Counter target noncreature spell.
cards.flavor: "The ancient kor were a clever bunch with a taste for nasty traps. Spikes, poison, fire pouring forth with no warning . . . I've seen and disabled them all. If you intend to raid a Skyclave, you'd be wise to hire me on."

cards.name: Spark Double
cards.text: You may have Spark Double enter the battlefield as a copy of a creature or planeswalker you control, except it enters with an additional +1/+1 counter on it if it's a creature, it enters with an additional loyalty counter on it if it's a planeswalker, and it isn't legendary.

cards.name: Tribute Mage
cards.text: When Tribute Mage enters the battlefield, you may search your library for an artifact card with mana value 2, reveal that card, put it into your hand, then shuffle.

cards.name: Blasphemous Act
cards.text:
This spell costs {1} less to cast for each creature on the battlefield.
Blasphemous Act deals 13 damage to each creature.
cards.flavor:
"Holy places are no longer sanctuary from death, and death is no longer sanctuary from anything."
-Thalia, Knight-Cathar

cards.name: Daretti, Scrap Savant
cards.text:
[+2]: Discard up to two cards, then draw that many cards.
[−2]: Sacrifice an artifact. If you do, return target artifact card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
[−10]: You get an emblem with "Whenever an artifact is put into your graveyard from the battlefield, return that card to the battlefield at the beginning of the next end step."
Daretti, Scrap Savant can be your commander.

cards.name: Fiery Gambit
cards.text: Flip a coin until you lose a flip or choose to stop flipping. If you lose a flip, Fiery Gambit has no effect. If you win one or more flips, Fiery Gambit deals 3 damage to target creature. If you win two or more flips, Fiery Gambit deals 6 damage to each opponent. If you win three or more flips, draw nine cards and untap all lands you control.

cards.name: Goblin Archaeologist
cards.text: {R}, {T}: Flip a coin. If you win the flip, destroy target artifact and untap Goblin Archaeologist. If you lose the flip, sacrifice Goblin Archaeologist.
cards.flavor: Always easily impressed, Durg was about to be blown away.

cards.name: Goblin Kaboomist
cards.text: At the beginning of your upkeep, create a colorless artifact token named Land Mine with "{R}, Sacrifice this artifact: This artifact deals 2 damage to target attacking creature without flying." Then flip a coin. If you lose the flip, Goblin Kaboomist deals 2 damage to itself.
cards.flavor: Designed by Stone Librande

cards.name: Karplusan Minotaur
cards.text:
Cumulative upkeep-Flip a coin. (At the beginning of your upkeep, put an age counter on this permanent, then sacrifice it unless you pay its upkeep cost for each age counter on it.)
Whenever you win a coin flip, Karplusan Minotaur deals 1 damage to any target.
Whenever you lose a coin flip, Karplusan Minotaur deals 1 damage to any target of an opponent's choice.

cards.name: Krark, the Thumbless
cards.text:
Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, flip a coin. If you lose the flip, return that spell to its owner's hand. If you win the flip, copy that spell, and you may choose new targets for the copy.
Partner (You can have two commanders if both have partner.)
cards.flavor: "Double or nothing."

cards.name: Tavern Scoundrel
cards.text:
Whenever you win a coin flip, create two Treasure tokens. (They're artifacts with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
{1}, {T}, Sacrifice another permanent: Flip a coin.
cards.flavor: "No refunds. I cheated you fair and square."

cards.name: Frenetic Sliver
cards.text: All Slivers have "{0}: If this permanent is on the battlefield, flip a coin. If you win the flip, exile this permanent and return it to the battlefield under its owner's control at the beginning of the next end step. If you lose the flip, sacrifice it."

cards.name: Niv-Mizzet, Parun
cards.text:
This spell can't be countered.
Flying
Whenever you draw a card, Niv-Mizzet, Parun deals 1 damage to any target.
Whenever a player casts an instant or sorcery spell, you draw a card.

cards.name: Ral Zarek
cards.text:
[+1]: Tap target permanent, then untap another target permanent.
[−2]: Ral Zarek deals 3 damage to any target.
[−7]: Flip five coins. Take an extra turn after this one for each coin that comes up heads.

cards.name: Izzet Signet
cards.flavor: The Izzet signet is redesigned often, each time becoming closer to a vanity portrait of Niv-Mizzet.

cards.name: Lightning Greaves
cards.text:
Equipped creature has haste and shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
Equip {0}
cards.flavor: After lightning struck the cliffs, the ore became iron, the iron became steel, and the steel became greaves. The lightning never left.

cards.name: Mind Stone
cards.text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}, {T}, Sacrifice Mind Stone: Draw a card.
cards.flavor:
"What is mana but possibility, an idea not yet given form?"
-Jhoira, master artificer

cards.name: Swiftfoot Boots
cards.text:
Equipped creature has hexproof and haste. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities your opponents control.)
Equip {1}
cards.flavor:
"There is great wisdom in rushing headlong into combat . . . if you're prepared."
-Kenjek, captain of the Thousand Swords

cards.name: Sword of Vengeance
cards.text:
Equipped creature gets +2/+0 and has first strike, vigilance, trample, and haste.
Equip {3}
cards.flavor: When wielded by a true believer, it matters little whether the sword is a relic or a replica.

cards.name: Thought Vessel
cards.text:
You have no maximum hand size.
{T}: Add {C}.
cards.flavor: Infinite possibilities contained in a finite space.

cards.name: Whispersilk Cloak
cards.text:
Equipped creature can't be blocked and has shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
Equip {2}

cards.name: Buried Ruin
cards.text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{2}, {T}, Sacrifice Buried Ruin: Return target artifact card from your graveyard to your hand.
cards.flavor: History has buried its treasures deep.

cards.name: Great Furnace
cards.text: {T}: Add {R}.
cards.flavor: Kuldotha, wellspring of molten metal, temple of the goblin horde.

cards.name: Izzet Boilerworks
cards.text:
Izzet Boilerworks enters the battlefield tapped.
When Izzet Boilerworks enters the battlefield, return a land you control to its owner's hand.
{T}: Add {U}{R}.

cards.name: Myriad Landscape
cards.text:
Myriad Landscape enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add {C}.
{2}, {T}, Sacrifice Myriad Landscape: Search your library for up to two basic land cards that share a land type, put them onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.

cards.name: Path of Ancestry
cards.text:
Path of Ancestry enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity. When that mana is spent to cast a creature spell that shares a creature type with your commander, scry 1. (Look at the top card of your library. You may put that card on the bottom of your library.)

cards.name: Rogue's Passage
cards.text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{4}, {T}: Target creature can't be blocked this turn.
cards.flavor: Rumors quickly spread among thieves about a labyrinth without walls and a prize beyond all measures of worth.

cards.name: Temple of Epiphany
cards.text:
Temple of Epiphany enters the battlefield tapped.
When Temple of Epiphany enters the battlefield, scry 1.
{T}: Add {U} or {R}.

cards.name: Wandering Fumarole
cards.text:
Wandering Fumarole enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add {U} or {R}.
{2}{U}{R}: Until end of turn, Wandering Fumarole becomes a 1/4 blue and red Elemental creature with "{0}: Switch this creature's power and toughness until end of turn." It's still a land.

cards.name: Counterspell
cards.text: Counter target spell.

cards.name: Long-Term Plans
cards.text: Search your library for a card, then shuffle and put that card third from the top.
cards.flavor: "Wait, it'll come to me in a minute."

cards.name: Muddle the Mixture
cards.text:
Counter target instant or sorcery spell.
Transmute {1}{U}{U} ({1}{U}{U}, Discard this card: Search your library for a card with the same mana value as this card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle. Transmute only as a sorcery.)

cards.name: Ponder
cards.text:
Look at the top three cards of your library, then put them back in any order. You may shuffle.
Draw a card.
cards.flavor: Tomorrow belongs to those who prepare for it today.

cards.name: Preordain
cards.text: Scry 2, then draw a card. (To scry 2, look at the top two cards of your library, then put any number of them on the bottom of your library and the rest on top in any order.)

cards.name: Reshape
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice an artifact.
Search your library for an artifact card with mana value X or less, put it onto the battlefield, then shuffle.
cards.flavor:
"Today's paperweight, tomorrow's leveler."
-Bruenna, Neurok leader

cards.name: Sakashima the Impostor
cards.text: You may have Sakashima the Impostor enter the battlefield as a copy of any creature on the battlefield, except its name is Sakashima the Impostor, it's legendary in addition to its other types, and it has "{2}{U}{U}: Return this creature to its owner's hand at the beginning of the next end step."

cards.name: Serum Visions
cards.text: Draw a card. Scry 2.
cards.flavor: Serum was once derived from Mirrodin's blinkmoths, offering visions of inspiration. Now it is pulled from Phyrexian inkmoths, yielding visions of perfection.

cards.name: Slip Through Space
cards.text:
Devoid (This card has no color.)
Target creature can't be blocked this turn.
Draw a card.
cards.flavor: The Eldrazi twisted in a direction that had no name, and a frontal assault became a panicked rout.

cards.name: Whir of Invention
cards.text:
Improvise (Your artifacts can help cast this spell. Each artifact you tap after you're done activating mana abilities pays for {1}.)
Search your library for an artifact card with mana value X or less, put it onto the battlefield, then shuffle.

cards.name: Bloodsworn Steward
cards.text:
Flying
Commander creatures you control get +2/+2 and have haste.
cards.flavor: "My liege will lead and I will follow-to the battlefield, to the grave, and beyond."

cards.name: Chance Encounter
cards.text:
Whenever you win a coin flip, put a luck counter on Chance Encounter.
At the beginning of your upkeep, if Chance Encounter has ten or more luck counters on it, you win the game.
cards.flavor: The more unlikely the victory, the more memorable the success.

cards.name: Chandra's Ignition
cards.text: Target creature you control deals damage equal to its power to each other creature and each opponent.
cards.flavor: In the moment before her execution, she realized what it meant to be a pyromancer, to be alive, to be Chandra.

cards.name: Chaos Warp
cards.text: The owner of target permanent shuffles it into their library, then reveals the top card of their library. If it's a permanent card, they put it onto the battlefield.

cards.name: Embercleave
cards.text:
Flash
This spell costs {1} less to cast for each attacking creature you control.
When Embercleave enters the battlefield, attach it to target creature you control.
Equipped creature gets +1/+1 and has double strike and trample.
Equip {3}

cards.name: Footfall Crater
cards.text:
Enchant land
Enchanted land has "{T}: Target creature gains trample and haste until end of turn."
Cycling {1} ({1}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

cards.name: Gamble
cards.text: Search your library for a card, put that card into your hand, discard a card at random, then shuffle.
cards.flavor:
"STUFF AND SUNDRIES AND MUNITIONS!"
-Breeches, gunner of the Belligerent

cards.name: Goblin Engineer
cards.text:
When Goblin Engineer enters the battlefield, you may search your library for an artifact card, put it into your graveyard, then shuffle.
{R}, {T}, Sacrifice an artifact: Return target artifact card with mana value 3 or less from your graveyard to the battlefield.

cards.name: Impulsive Maneuvers
cards.text: Whenever a creature attacks, flip a coin. If you win the flip, the next time that creature would deal combat damage this turn, it deals double that damage instead. If you lose the flip, the next time that creature would deal combat damage this turn, prevent that damage.

cards.name: Mirror March
cards.text: Whenever a nontoken creature enters the battlefield under your control, flip a coin until you lose a flip. For each flip you won, create a token that's a copy of that creature. Those tokens gain haste. Exile them at the beginning of the next end step.

cards.name: Mogg Assassin
cards.text: {T}: You choose target creature an opponent controls, and that opponent chooses target creature. Flip a coin. If you win the flip, destroy the creature you chose. If you lose the flip, destroy the creature your opponent chose.

cards.name: Planar Chaos
cards.text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, flip a coin. If you lose the flip, sacrifice Planar Chaos.
Whenever a player casts a spell, that player flips a coin. If they lose the flip, counter that spell.

cards.name: Risky Move
cards.text:
At the beginning of each player's upkeep, that player gains control of Risky Move.
When you gain control of Risky Move from another player, choose a creature you control and an opponent. Flip a coin. If you lose the flip, that opponent gains control of that creature.

cards.name: Seize the Day
cards.text:
Untap target creature. After this main phase, there is an additional combat phase followed by an additional main phase.
Flashback {2}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

cards.name: Temur Battle Rage
cards.text:
Target creature gains double strike until end of turn.
Ferocious - That creature also gains trample until end of turn if you control a creature with power 4 or greater.

cards.name: Vandalblast
cards.text:
Destroy target artifact you don't control.
Overload {4}{R} (You may cast this spell for its overload cost. If you do, change its text by replacing all instances of "target" with "each.")
cards.flavor: Beauty is in the eye of the exploder.

cards.name: The Locust God
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever you draw a card, create a 1/1 blue and red Insect creature token with flying and haste.
{2}{U}{R}: Draw a card, then discard a card.
When The Locust God dies, return it to its owner's hand at the beginning of the next end step.

cards.name: Squee's Revenge
cards.text: Choose a number. Flip a coin that many times or until you lose a flip, whichever comes first. If you win all the flips, draw two cards for each flip.

cards.name: Yusri, Fortune's Flame
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever Yusri, Fortune's Flame attacks, choose a number between 1 and 5. Flip that many coins. For each flip you win, draw a card. For each flip you lose, Yusri deals 2 damage to you. If you won five flips this way, you may cast spells from your hand this turn without paying their mana costs.

cards.name: Arcane Signet
cards.text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
cards.flavor: It started as a mere drop of water. The Magic Mirror crystallized it into much more.

cards.name: Boompile
cards.text: {T}: Flip a coin. If you win the flip, destroy all nonland permanents.
cards.flavor:
"Fuses? We have more than enough! Now . . . which one was it?"
-Flearan One-Eye, goblin engineer

cards.name: Commander's Plate
cards.text:
Equipped creature gets +3/+3 and has protection from each color that's not in your commander's color identity.
Equip commander {3}
Equip {5}
cards.flavor: Not all beautiful things are fragile.

cards.name: Crooked Scales
cards.text: {4}, {T}: Flip a coin. If you win the flip, destroy target creature an opponent controls. If you lose the flip, destroy target creature you control unless you pay {3} and repeat this process.

cards.name: Shadowspear
cards.text:
Equipped creature gets +1/+1 and has trample and lifelink.
{1}: Permanents your opponents control lose hexproof and indestructible until end of turn.
Equip {2}
cards.flavor: A weapon of darkness for a warrior of light.

cards.name: Sol Ring
cards.text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.
cards.flavor: Lost to time is the artificer's art of trapping light from a distant star in a ring of purest gold.

cards.name: Talisman of Creativity
cards.text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{T}: Add {U} or {R}. Talisman of Creativity deals 1 damage to you.
cards.flavor:
"Good ideas don't take time. They take a lot of bad ideas first."
-Ral Zarek

cards.name: Academy Ruins
cards.text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}{U}, {T}: Put target artifact card from your graveyard on top of your library.
cards.flavor: Its secrets once wrought the greatest artifice ever known. Now crabs loot the rubble to decorate their shells.

cards.name: Cascade Bluffs

cards.flavor: Travelers bathe in the falls to wash away curses from the pucas who lurk nearby.

cards.name: Command Tower
cards.text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
cards.flavor:
"Approach my tower on bended knee or depart from it as ash upon the wind."
-Gadwick, the Wizened

cards.name: Desolate Lighthouse
cards.text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}{U}{R}, {T}: Draw a card, then discard a card.
cards.flavor: A lonely sentinel facing gales, hurricanes, and tides of homicidal spirits.

cards.flavor:
"It was a strange morning. When we awoke, we found our trees transformed. We didn't know whether to water them or polish them."
-Pulan, Bant orchardist
